seller_notes: QR Code Link to This Post Selling my 2010 GTI . I bought this car mid pandemic because prices were so high for new cars and I wanted something fun to drive while I waited for prices to become more reasonable. Love the car and it’s still my daily so miles will be going up. That being said I work remotely so won’t be going up too much too fast.  If you are looking for a car in perfect cosmetic condition this car is not for you. I tried to get pictures of the cosmetic issues as best as I could. That being said mechanically it’s doing great!  The bad:  - Scratches on the outside some longer ones.  - Few dings around the car. Very small though.  - Headliner was drooping. I fixed it myself (see pics) and it looks great but it obviously isn’t factory perfect. Looked into getting it fixed professionally and was quoted multiple thousands so was not worth it.  - Inside plastic piece by the shifter is faded and mis colored.  - needs an alignment, will probably have one done by the time you come to see it but mentioning it just in case -wheels are all curbed. Doesn’t look great but they are the original wheels.  All of these things were issues when I bought the car so can’t speak to where they came from or when they happened.  The good:  -low miles considering the year  -Engine, transmission, turbo etc all in great shape. Drives great -Recently changed the radiator, fluids, oil, rear main seal -timing chain replaced (prior to me purchasing)  -cylinder head was rebuilt on this car (prior to me purchasing) If you know these cars then you know there is a defect from the factory with the timing chains and tensioners that can cause major engine damage. Whether u buy mine or another one, please check for this being done already and if another, replace the chain and tensioner with a newer one asap to avoid this issue. Anything with this done already is a much safer bet.  -My mechanic is an expert on these cars and knows this car well as he has done all the work on it and actually even sold me the car. I can share his contact if you are interested or in need of a reliable mechanic regardless of if you buy the car. He specializes in VW, Audi, Porsche but works on almost all cars I think.  Email me or chat with me in the app if interested and I can get you more info and my number. Buyer must either have cash or certified check. Make me an offer.
